	the 
	<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table"/> 
	used to derive the colour.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: colour_association_table
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table">
	A <b>colour_association_table</b> is a mapping of a one-dimensional state variable space into a colour space.
	<p>
	The <b>colour_association_table</b> contains state variable values that are associated with a colour. 
	When the value of a state variable is between two fixed state variable values, the colour shall be calculated by either staircase or linear interpolation.
	</p>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_association_table.discrete_states_with_colours
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table.discrete_states_with_colours"> 
	a list of one-dimensional state variable values that are associated with colour.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: colour_association_table.interpolation_type
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.colour_association_table.interpolation_type"> 
	the method of interpolation to be used.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: state_variable_with_colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.state_variable_with_colour">
	A <b>state_variable_with_colour</b> is an association of a single fixed state variable with a 
	<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_specification"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: state_variable_with_colour.state_variable
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.state_variable_with_colour.state_variable"> 
<p>
	the value of a one-dimensional <b>state_variable</b>.
</p>
	<example>
  		Physical state variables are temperature and stress components.
  	</example>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Subobject: state_variable_with_colour.associated_colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.state_variable_with_colour.associated_colour"> 
	the 
	<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour_specification"/> 
	associated with the <b>state_variable</b>.
</ext_description>



<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
ENTITY: pre_defined_colour
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="presentation_resource_schema.pre_defined_colour">
	A <b>pre_defined_colour</b> is a type of
	<express_ref linkend="presentation_resource_schema:ir_express:presentation_resource_schema.colour"/>
	and a type of
	<express_ref linkend="external_reference_schema:ir_express:external_reference_schema.pre_defined_item"/>.
	A <b>pre_defined_colour</b> is provided to allow an application-specific colour definition.
	<note>
		Application Resources or Application Protocols specify the use of this entity.
	    The <b>pre_defined_colour</b> entity further enables Application 
	    Resources or Application Protocols to fix colour values or components
	    of colour values for their particular uses.
	</note>
</ext_description>

